documentation.text: @dev EthProxy allows users to post and withdraw Eth to the Controller, which will be converted to and from Weth in the process.
@dev The WETH9 contract will send ether to EthProxy on `_weth.withdraw` using this function.
@dev EthProxy allows users to post and withdraw Eth to the Controller, which will be converted to and from Weth in the process.
@dev The WETH9 contract will send ether to EthProxy on `_weth.withdraw` using this function.

devdoc.details: EthProxy allows users to post and withdraw Eth to the Controller, which will be converted to and from Weth in the process.

post(address,uint256).details: Users use `post` in EthProxy to post ETH to the Controller, which will be converted to Weth here.

params.to: Yield Vault to deposit collateral in.

withdraw(address,uint256).details: Users wishing to withdraw their Weth as ETH from the Controller should use this function. Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(ethProxy.address)` to authorize EthProxy to act in their behalf.

withdrawBySignature(address,uint256,uint.details: Users wishing to withdraw their Weth as ETH from the Controller should use this function. Users must supply an encoded signature for Controller add EthProxy as a delegate.

params.deadline: Latest block timestamp for which the signature is valid
